== CodeSelect over lengtht mobile after edit ==
* see screenshot provided (non-blocking)

'''DEV'''
* Dev can reproduce bug only by changing screen size after loading
* But this is expected.
* The codeselect scroll bar is loaded only at page load time. After that we would need an Observer to change JS scrollbar if the screen size changes. And that would slow the page performance, because we would need it for every scrollbar
* {{IconSet|h3|Handling suggestions}}
*# Ignore issue, because it's only if screen size changes, which is not very often (only if mobile users rotate screen, which they usually only do for videos/photos or if the page is not optimized for portrait mode, but which our wikis are)
*# Have ONE screen size observer. Once screen size chance, reload the whole page (so every Javascript is loaded again and everything fits perfectly again) - little work, but not recommended
*# Have ONE screen size observer. Add a refresh/re-initialization method in all relevant scripts which change optics in a significant way like scrollbars - a lot of work, but recommended IF ignoring is no option

